SIEM Lab: Splunk on Kali Linux
📌 Overview

This project demonstrates the installation, configuration, and troubleshooting of Splunk Enterprise on a Kali Linux virtual machine.

The goal of this lab is to simulate real-world SOC analyst tasks, including:

SIEM deployment
Service troubleshooting
Log monitoring preparation
🎯 Objectives
Install Splunk Enterprise on Kali Linux
Resolve installation and startup issues
Configure Splunk to run persistently at boot
Validate web interface and service availability
Prepare environment for log ingestion and threat detection
🧰 Technologies Used
Kali Linux (VirtualBox)
Splunk Enterprise
Linux CLI (bash)
Systemd (service management)
⚙️ Installation Steps
1. Download Splunk
wget -O splunk.deb "https://download.splunk.com/products/splunk/releases/10.2.1/linux/splunk-10.2.1-c892b66d163d-linux-amd64.deb"
2. Install Package
sudo dpkg -i splunk.deb
sudo apt --fix-broken install -y
3. Start Splunk
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk start --accept-license
🔧 Troubleshooting (Key Learning)

During setup, several real-world issues occurred:

❌ Issue 1: Command Errors
Incorrect syntax caused “command not found”
Fixed by correcting Linux command usage
❌ Issue 2: Splunk Not Starting
splunkd is not running
Root cause: permission and execution conflicts

✔️ Fix:

sudo chown -R ray:ray /opt/splunk
/opt/splunk/bin/splunk start
❌ Issue 3: Web Interface Not Accessible
localhost:8000 refused to connect

✔️ Fix:

Verified Splunk status
Used correct address:
http://127.0.0.1:8000
❌ Issue 4: Boot Service Failure
Splunk failed to start at boot due to root execution

✔️ Fix:

sudo /opt/splunk/bin/splunk enable boot-start -user ray
✅ Verification

Check Splunk status:

/opt/splunk/bin/splunk status

Expected output:

splunkd is running

Access Web Interface:

http://127.0.0.1:8000
🔁 Persistence Test

Reboot system:

sudo reboot

Verify:

/opt/splunk/bin/splunk status

✔️ Splunk starts automatically at boot

